{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Ibn Majah","section":{"8":"The Chapters Regarding Zakat"},"section_detail":{"8":{"hadithnumber_first":1783,"hadithnumber_last":1844,"arabicnumber_first":1783,"arabicnumber_last":1844}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1825,"arabicnumber":1825,"text":"Rapporté par Ibn Umar : Le Messager d’Allah a prescrit la Zakat al-Fitr, un Sa de dattes ou un Sa d’orge. Abdullah a dit : Les gens ont pris deux Mudd (soit la moitié d’un Sa) de blé comme équivalent","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih - Bukhari And Muslim"}],"reference":{"book":8,"hadith":43}}]}